      {
        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "### Why?\n\nNIST SRD-46 (the **NIST Critically Selected Stability Constants of Metal Complexes**) is specifically curated for **aqueous-phase** thermodynamic data. Supercritical CO₂ complexation studies do exist in the research literature (e.g., metal–β-diketonate or metal–organophosphorus complexes in scCO₂ for extraction applications), but they fall outside the scope of this particular database.\n\n**If you need scCO₂ stability data**, you would need to search the primary literature directly (e.g., via SciFinder, Web of Science) or specialized reviews on supercritical fluid extraction chemistry.\n\n*Source: NIST SRD-46*",
